Interviewer 1: That high, okay. Therefore, if there was a patient with ten, maybe twenty percent chance of success, would that be an exclusion criterion for you?
Respondent: That is a mean question. I remember the doctors telling me, I had a 1% chance of survival when I had my daughter, and I did survive. It would’ve been a pity if they gave up, just because of a percentage. Therefore, I think, everybody should get a chance regardless. – Interview 07
